columns.name: X
columns.description: Longitude coordinate for squirrel sighting point

columns.name: Y
columns.description: Latitude coordinate for squirrel sighting point

columns.name: Unique Squirrel ID
columns.description: Identification tag for each squirrel sightings. The tag is comprised of "Hectare ID" + "Shift" + "Date" + "Hectare Squirrel Number."

columns.name: Hectare
columns.description: ID tag, which is derived from the hectare grid used to divide and count the park area. One axis that runs predominantly north-to-south is numerical (1-42), and the axis that runs predominantly east-to-west is roman characters (A-I).

columns.name: Shift
columns.description: Value is either "AM" or "PM," to communicate whether or not the sighting session occurred in the morning or late afternoon.

columns.name: Date
columns.description: Concatenation of the sighting session day and month.

columns.name: Hectare Squirrel Number
columns.description: Number within the chronological sequence of squirrel sightings for a discrete sighting session.

columns.name: Age
columns.description: Value is either "Adult" or "Juvenile."

columns.name: Primary Fur Color
columns.description: Value is either "Gray," "Cinnamon" or "Black."

columns.name: Highlight Fur Color
columns.description: Discrete value or string values comprised of "Gray," "Cinnamon" or "Black."

columns.name: Combination of Primary and Highlight Color
columns.description: A combination of the previous two columns this column gives the total permutations of primary and highlight colors observed.

columns.name: Color notes
columns.description: Sighters occasionally added commentary on the squirrel fur conditions. These notes are provided here.

top.item: Gray & Cinnamon selected as Primary. White selected as Highlights. Made executive adjustments.
Gray & Cinnamon selected as Primary. Nothing selected as Highlights. Made executive adjustments.
Nothing selected as Primary. Gray selected as Highlights. Made executive adjustments.
Gray & Cinnamon selected as Primary. Cinnamon & White selected as Highlights. Made executive adjustments.
Gray & Cinnamon selected as Primary. Gray & White selected as Highlights. Made executive adjustments.
Listed as primary white with cinnamon highlights, I changed to Gray/cinnamon - JO
Gray & Cinnamon selected as Primary. Cinnamon selected as Highlights. Made executive adjustments.
Gray, Cinnamon & White selected as Primary. Gray & White selected as Highlights. Made executive adjustments.
Gray, Black, & Cinnamon selected as Primary. Gray, Cinnamon, & White selected as Highlights. Made executive adjustments.

columns.name: Location
columns.description: Value is either "Ground Plane" or "Above Ground." Sighters were instructed to indicate the location of where the squirrel was when first sighted.

columns.name: Above Ground Sighter Measurement
columns.description: For squirrel sightings on the ground plane, fields were populated with a value of “FALSE.”

columns.name: Specific Location
columns.description: Sighters occasionally added commentary on the squirrel location. These notes are provided here.

top.item: small open area but w/ 7 large oak trees

columns.name: Running
columns.description: Squirrel was seen running.

columns.name: Chasing
columns.description: Squirrel was seen chasing another squirrel.

columns.name: Climbing
columns.description: Squirrel was seen climbing a tree or other environmental landmark.

columns.name: Eating
columns.description: Squirrel was seen eating.

columns.name: Foraging
columns.description: Squirrel was seen foraging for food.

columns.name: Kuks
columns.description: Squirrel was heard kukking, a chirpy vocal communication used for a variety of reasons.

columns.name: Quaas
columns.description: Squirrel was heard quaaing, an elongated vocal communication which can indicate the presence of a ground predator such as a dog.

columns.name: Moans
columns.description: Squirrel was heard moaning, a high-pitched vocal communication which can indicate the presence of an air predator such as a hawk.

columns.name: Tail flags
columns.description: Squirrel was seen flagging its tail. Flagging is a whipping motion used to exaggerate squirrel's size and confuse rivals or predators. Looks as if the squirrel is scribbling with tail into the air.

columns.name: Tail twitches
columns.description: Squirrel was seen twitching its tail. Looks like a wave running through the tail, like a breakdancer doing the arm wave. Often used to communicate interest, curiosity.

columns.name: Approaches
columns.description: Squirrel was seen approaching human, seeking food.

columns.name: Indifferent
columns.description: Squirrel was indifferent to human presence.

columns.name: Runs from
columns.description: Squirrel was seen running from humans, seeing them as a threat.

columns.name: Other Interactions
columns.description: Sighter notes on other types of interactions between squirrels and humans.

view.description: The Squirrel Census (https://www.thesquirrelcensus.com/) is a multimedia science, design, and storytelling project focusing on the Eastern gray (Sciurus carolinensis). They count squirrels and present their findings to the public. This table contains squirrel data for each of the 3,023 sightings, including location coordinates, age, primary and secondary fur color, elevation, activities, communications, and interactions between squirrels and with humans.
